---
/**
 * banner-anatomy — Chapter 081 Lesson 5, "Nothing fires pre-consent".
 *
 * An annotated mock of the three-button consent banner. The whole point is to
 * make the dark-pattern rule VISIBLE: "Reject all" and "Accept all" must be the
 * exact same size, prominence, and visual weight — asymmetry there is the thing
 * regulators (CNIL, EDPB) fine. So the mock paints all three buttons identically
 * and color-keyed callouts name what each part guarantees.
 *
 * Per the diagram index, this is an "annotated illustration" → HTML + CSS, with
 * color-matched callouts instead of arrows (the index's "color match beats
 * arrows" guidance for tight UI mocks). Three accents:
 *
 *   - amber  (#d97706) — the compliance-critical equal-weight pair; the dominant
 *     callout. Both Accept/Reject buttons carry an amber outline so the eye ties
 *     the callout to the pair it governs.
 *   - blue   (#0ea5e9) — "Manage preferences" → the per-category toggle modal.
 *   - teal   (#0d9488) — the non-modal sticky-footer placement (the bar itself).
 *
 * Saturated mid-tones + white/own-color text so the keying survives both themes;
 * all chrome uses Starlight CSS vars. Scoped <style>, matching the sibling
 * PreConsentTimeline in this folder.
 */
import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
---

<Figure caption="Three buttons, equal weight. The one thing that gets teams fined is making Accept easier than Reject.">
	<div class="ba">
		{/* ── The mock banner: a non-modal sticky footer bar ─────────────────── */}
		<div class="ba-bar">
			<span class="ba-bar-tag">sticky footer</span>
			<p class="ba-copy">
				We use cookies to measure and improve the product. You choose what's on.
			</p>
			<div class="ba-buttons">
				<button type="button" class="ba-btn ba-btn--weight">Reject all</button>
				<button type="button" class="ba-btn ba-btn--manage">Manage preferences</button>
				<button type="button" class="ba-btn ba-btn--weight">Accept all</button>
			</div>
		</div>

		{/* ── Color-keyed callouts, matched to the parts above ────────────────── */}
		<div class="ba-notes">
			<div class="ba-note ba-note--weight">
				<span class="ba-swatch"></span>
				<div class="ba-note-body">
					<strong>Equal weight</strong> — same size, same prominence, same one click for
					&ldquo;Reject all&rdquo; and &ldquo;Accept all&rdquo;. Asymmetry here is the dark
					pattern regulators fine.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="ba-note ba-note--manage">
				<span class="ba-swatch"></span>
				<div class="ba-note-body">
					<strong>Manage preferences</strong> opens a modal with the two category toggles
					(<code>analytics</code>, <code>marketing</code>) — both default-off.
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="ba-note ba-note--bar">
				<span class="ba-swatch"></span>
				<div class="ba-note-body">
					<strong>Non-modal sticky footer</strong> — a modest bar, never a full-page wall
					that holds the content hostage.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Figure>

<style>
	.ba {
		--ba-weight: #d97706; /* compliance-critical equal-weight pair */
		--ba-manage: #0ea5e9; /* the Manage → toggle-modal path */
		--ba-bar: #0d9488; /* non-modal sticky-footer placement */
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.25rem;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* ── Banner bar ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
	.ba-bar {
		position: relative;
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
		padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
		border: 2px solid var(--ba-bar);
		border-radius: 12px;
		background: var(--sl-color-bg);
		box-shadow: 0 6px 18px -10px color-mix(in srgb, var(--ba-bar) 60%, transparent);
		margin: 0;
	}
	/* "fieldset legend" tag straddling the bar's top border. */
	.ba-bar-tag {
		display: block;
		width: fit-content;
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 1rem;
		transform: translateY(-50%);
		padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar);
		color: var(--ba-bar);
		border: 1px solid var(--ba-bar);
		font-size: 0.62rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.ba-copy {
		flex: 1 1 14rem;
		min-width: 0;
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.92rem;
		line-height: 1.4;
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
	}
	.ba-buttons {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.6rem;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.ba-btn {
		margin: 0;
		font: inherit;
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 0.5rem 0.95rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
		cursor: pointer;
		white-space: nowrap;
		/* All three buttons share the SAME baseline so nothing reads as primary. */
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-3);
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-6);
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
	}
	/* The equal-weight pair: identical fill, amber outline tying them to the
	   callout. Both look exactly alike — that sameness is the lesson. */
	.ba-btn--weight {
		border-color: var(--ba-weight);
		box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px color-mix(in srgb, var(--ba-weight) 26%, transparent);
	}
	.ba-btn--manage {
		border-color: var(--ba-manage);
		box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px color-mix(in srgb, var(--ba-manage) 26%, transparent);
	}

	/* ── Color-keyed callouts ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
	.ba-notes {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(15rem, 1fr));
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.ba-note {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-start;
		gap: 0.6rem;
		padding: 0.7rem 0.8rem;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
		border-left-width: 4px;
		background: var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.ba-swatch {
		flex: none;
		width: 0.85rem;
		height: 0.85rem;
		border-radius: 3px;
		margin: 0.15rem 0 0;
	}
	.ba-note-body {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		line-height: 1.4;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
	}
	.ba-note-body strong {
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
	}
	.ba-note-body code {
		font-size: 0.85em;
	}

	/* The dominant, compliance-critical callout. */
	.ba-note--weight {
		border-color: var(--ba-weight);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--ba-weight) 10%, var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar));
		grid-column: 1 / -1;
	}
	.ba-note--weight .ba-swatch {
		background: var(--ba-weight);
		width: 1rem;
		height: 1rem;
	}
	.ba-note--weight .ba-note-body {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--sl-color-white);
	}

	.ba-note--manage {
		border-left-color: var(--ba-manage);
	}
	.ba-note--manage .ba-swatch {
		background: var(--ba-manage);
	}
	.ba-note--bar {
		border-left-color: var(--ba-bar);
	}
	.ba-note--bar .ba-swatch {
		background: var(--ba-bar);
	}
</style>
